                        <summary>
                            <p><bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1920-1921"/></bibl> (ARIE/1920-1921/C/1921/27): <quote>Vijayanagara. Kampaṇa-Uḍaiyār, son of Vīra Bokkaṇa Uḍaiyār. Śaka 128[9*], Pḷavaṅga, Mēsha, śu., ēkādaśi, Monday, Uttiram. On the south wall of the second <foreign>prākāra</foreign> of the same temple. States that the king while seated in the Jānakī-maṇḍapa granted to Śrī Parakāla-Nambi the name of Karuṇākara-dāśaṉ with certain honours, privileges and a dwelling house.</quote></p>
                            <p>Inscription not found in 2024 in the temple.</p>                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
